### 2. Path-Aware Semantic Addressing (PASA) for Low power and Lossy Networks
* **Presenter:** Luigi Iannone
* **Slide Deck:** [Path-Aware Semantic Addressing (PASA) for Low power and Lossy Networks](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-6lo-path-aware-semantic-addressing-pasa-for-low-power-and-lossy-networks-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * Since the last IETF, two revisions were published to address reviews by Hong Yang and Éric Vyncke. Changes included terminology improvements, algorithm clarifications, and security considerations based on RFC 4443 (ICMPv6 error handling).
  * **Use Cases Section:** Éric Vyncke suggested moving the extensive use cases section to an appendix to make the document lighter. Luigi agreed to this change.
  * **Intended Status (Proposed Standard vs. Experimental):** Reviews raised concerns that the technology might be too disruptive/new for a Proposed Standard. Éric Vyncke suggested that changing the status to Experimental would ease the IESG evaluation process. Laurent Toutain noted that changing to Experimental requires defining the concrete experiment and its intended outcomes in the document. Luigi agreed and indicated that an internal implementation is ongoing.

