### 3. Generic Address Assignment Option (GAAO) for 6LoWPAN Neighbor Discovery
* **Presenter:** Luigi Iannone
* **Slide Deck:** [Generic Address Assignment Option for 6LoWPAN Neighbor Discovery](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-6lo-generic-address-assignment-option-for-6lowpan-neighbor-discovery-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * Two revisions were submitted to address reviews. Appendix C was added to provide a comparison between GAAO and DHCPv6 tailored for 6LoWPAN deployments, including rapid commit options.
  * **Efficiency Concerns:** Laurent Toutain pointed out that the current introduction asserts DHCPv6 is inefficient, but Appendix C suggests DHCPv6 with rapid commit is almost as efficient, except for multi-link packet propagation. He suggested updating the introduction to reflect this and explaining why alternative designs (such as restricting DHCPv6 packet scope) were not pursued. Luigi Iannone agreed that efficiency is highly topology-dependent and agreed to refine the wording.
  * **Alternative Deployment Experiences:** Esco Dijk shared that a previous 6LoWPAN mesh network deployment had defined a unicast-based DHCPv6 operation to circumvent multicast inefficiencies, though it was not widely deployed due to SLAAC. Esco offered to send this reference to the authors.
  * Alexander Pelov encouraged the working group to perform additional reviews to help refine the scope and wording.

