### 4. Transmission of SCHC-Compressed Packets over IEEE 802.15.4 Networks
* **Presenter:** Carles Gomez
* **Slide Deck:** [Transmission of SCHC-compressed packets over IEEE 802.15.4 networks](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-6lo-transmission-of-schc-compressed-packets-over-ieee-802154-networks-00)
* **Draft Reference:** [draft-ietf-6lo-schc-15dot4](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-6lo-schc-15dot4/)
* **Discussion:**
  * The latest version (v13) addresses outstanding comments from Esco Dijk regarding the Pointer-Based Route-Over (PRO) mode. 
  * To resolve an encoding limitation of the Address Residue Length field (which needs to represent values from 0 to 128), the field size was reduced from 7 bits to 5 bits. It now maps values indirectly using a lookup table in Appendix C based on typical prefix sizes.
  * **Normative Content:** Éric Vyncke strongly advised moving this lookup table from Appendix C into the main body of the document because appendices are considered non-normative by default. Carles agreed to move it.
  * **SCHC Architecture Alignment:** Carles noted that version 06 of the SCHC Architecture draft introduced terminology changes (e.g., "control header", "instance" vs. "session"). The authors plan to align the terminology in the 15.4 draft with these updates. Alexander Pelov confirmed that the SCHC WG will coordinate with the authors to ensure a smooth transition.
  * Once the terminology is updated and the table is relocated, the document will be ready for Working Group Last Call (WGLC), which will also be shared with the SCHC working group.

